org.joda.primitives.collection.impl

Class ArrayBooleanCollection

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.joda.primitives.collection.impl.AbstractPrimitiveCollectable<Boolean>
      • org.joda.primitives.collection.impl.AbstractBooleanCollection
        • org.joda.primitives.collection.impl.ArrayBooleanCollection
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable, Iterable<Boolean>, Collection<Boolean>, BooleanCollection, PrimitiveCollection<Boolean>, BooleanIterable, PrimitiveCollectable<Boolean>

    public class ArrayBooleanCollection
extends AbstractBooleanCollection
implements Cloneable
    Array based implementation of BooleanCollection for primitive boolean elements.

    This collection implementation allows multiple copies of the same value to be added. Internally, it uses an array, and behaves much like a list.

    This class implements Collection allowing seamless integration with other APIs.

    Add, Remove and Clear are supported.

    Since:
    1.0
